  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "[LAUGHING] [?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "Litvinova. ?] And I got a letter from her.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And she told me when my father passed away.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "I was able to obtain a certificate of that from the doctor whom I found two days before he left Poland, and he sent it to me.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And my mother needed it later on when she got, when she remarried, here, in the United States, another refugee from Hungary who had lost his wife and four children at Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The only camp I really passed by was Majdanek.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "At the time, I wasn't aware what it is.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were at, that was-- there was a first few weeks when we were in action in July of 1944.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We had crossed the [?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Volga ?] River.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We had been greeted enthusiastically by the Poles when we came through there.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was a sunny day, and we-- suddenly, there's a whole convoy stop, because somewhere, always, a convoy gets into some trouble, and something happens.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we stopped just in front of a gate, which I remember, an iron gate which was open.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There was a fence surrounding the place, and I saw some construction, which turned out to be ovens from which there still was smoke coming out.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was only later that we found out that it was a notorious camp, Majdanek.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "When you stop, sitting high on a truck, and see something, you really don't know yet what it is until somebody later tells you what it was.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So that was the camp, there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We came through another-- not this kind of camp.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "An encampment where the Germans had been training foreign police-- Lithuanian, Estonian, Polish, from all those occupied countries where they needed policemen.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
